cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep learning approaches for video classification and recognition, specifically using 3-dimensional convolutions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for visualizing the spatio-temporal regions that the network finds most informative, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
